M|Skil|tx|> Learn how to write effective Skills that Claude can discover and use successfully.
M|Skil|tx|Good Skills are concise, well-structured, and tested w/ real usage. This guide provides practical authoring decisions to help you write Skills that Claude can discover and use effectively.
M|Skil|tx|For conceptual background on how Skills work, see the [Skills overview](/en/doc/ag-and-tools/ag-skills/overview).
M|Conc|The |//platform.claude.com/doc/en/bd-w/-claude/context-windows) is a public good. Your Skill shares the context window w/ everything else Claude needs to know, inc:
M|Conc|it|The sy pm
M|Conc|it|Conversation history
M|Conc|it|Other Skills' metadata
M|Conc|it|Your actual request
M|Conc|Not |once Claude loads it, every tk competes w/ conversation history and other context.
M|Conc|**De|Claude is already very smart
M|Conc|Only|
M|Conc|it|"Does Claude really need this explanation?"
M|Conc|it|"Can I assume Claude knows this?"
M|Conc|it|"Does this paragraph justify its tk cost?"
