M|Extr|tx|```markdown  theme={null}
M|Extr|tx|PDF (Portable Document Format) files are a common file format that contains
M|Extr|tx|text, images, and other cn. To extract text from a PDF, you'll need to
M|Extr|tx|use a library. There are many libraries available for PDF processing, but we
M|Extr|tx|recommend pdfplumber bc it's easy to use and handles most cases well.
M|Extr|tx|First, you'll need to install it using pip. Then you can use the code below...
M|Extr|tx|```
M|Extr|tx|The concise version assumes Claude knows what PDFs are and how libraries work.
