M|Adva|tx|Claude loads FORMS.md, REFERENCE.md, or EXAMPLES.md only when needed.
M|Patt|tx|For Skills w/ multiple domains, organize cn by domain to avoid loading irrelevant context. When a us asks abt sales metrics, Claude only needs to read sales-related schemas, not fi or mk data. This keeps tk usage lo and context focused.
M|Patt|tx|```
M|Patt|tx|bigquery-skill/
M|Patt|tx|├── SKILL.md (overview and navigation)
M|Patt|tx|└── reference/
M|Patt|tx|├── fi.md (rv, billing metrics)
M|Patt|tx|├── sales.md (opportunities, pipeline)
M|Patt|tx|├── pd.md (ap usage, features)
M|Patt|tx|└── mk.md (cg, attribution)
M|Patt|tx|```
M|Patt|tx|````markdown SKILL.md theme={null}
M|Avai|fi|rv, ARR, billing → See [reference/fi.md](reference/fi.md)
M|Avai|**Sa|Opportunities, pipeline, accounts → See [reference/sales.md](reference/sales.md)
M|Avai|pd|ap usage, features, adoption → See [reference/pd.md](reference/pd.md)
M|Avai|mk|cg, attribution, em → See [reference/mk.md](reference/mk.md)
M|Quic|Find|
M|Quic|tx|```bash
M|Quic|tx|grep -i "rv" reference/fi.md
M|Quic|tx|grep -i "pipeline" reference/sales.md
M|Quic|tx|grep -i "ap usage" reference/pd.md
M|Quic|tx|```
M|Quic|tx|````
