M|Edit|tx|```
M|Edit|tx|Claude reads REDLINING.md or OOXML.md only when the us needs those features.
M|Avoi|tx|Claude may partially read files when they're referenced from other referenced files. When encountering nested references, Claude might use commands like `head -100` to preview cn rather than reading entire files, resulting in incomplete information.
M|Avoi|tx|**Keep references one level deep from SKILL.md**. All reference files shd link directly from SKILL.md to ensure Claude reads complete files when needed.
M|Avoi|**Ba|Too deep**:
M|Avoi|tx|```markdown  theme={null}
M|SKIL|tx|See [advanced.md](advanced.md)...
M|adva|tx|See [details.md](details.md)...
M|deta|tx|Here's the actual information...
M|deta|tx|```
M|deta|**Go|One level deep**:
M|deta|tx|```markdown  theme={null}
M|SKIL|**Ba|[instructions in SKILL.md]
M|SKIL|**Ad|See [advanced.md](advanced.md)
M|SKIL|**AP|See [reference.md](reference.md)
M|SKIL|**Ex|See [examples.md](examples.md)
M|SKIL|tx|```
M|Stru|tx|For reference files longer than 100 lines, include a table of contents at the top. This ensures Claude can see the full scope of available information even when previewing w/ partial reads.
M|Stru|**Ex|
M|Stru|tx|```markdown  theme={null}
M|Cont|it|Authentication and setup
M|Cont|it|Core methods (cr, read, up, dl)
M|Cont|it|Advanced features (batch operations, webhooks)
M|Cont|it|er handling patterns
M|Cont|it|Code examples
M|Auth|tx|...
M|Core|tx|...
M|Core|tx|```
M|Core|tx|Claude can then read the complete file or jump to specific sections as needed.
M|Core|tx|For details on how this filesystem-based architecture enables progressive disclosure, see the [Runtime environment](#runtime-environment) section in the Advanced section below.
M|Use |tx|Break complex operations into clear, sequential steps. For particularly complex workflows, provide a checklist that Claude can cp into its rp and check off as it progresses.
M|Use |**Ex|Research synthesis workflow** (for Skills w/o code):
M|Use |tx|````markdown  theme={null}
M|Rese|Copy|
M|Rese|tx|```
M|Rese|Rese|
M|Rese|- [ |Read all source documents
M|Rese|- [ |Identify key themes
M|Rese|- [ |Cross-reference claims
M|Rese|- [ |cr structured summary
M|Rese|- [ |Verify citations
M|Rese|tx|```
M|Rese|**St|Read all source documents**
M|Rese|tx|rv each document in the `sources/` directory. Note the main arguments and supporting evidence.
M|Rese|**St|Identify key themes**
M|Rese|tx|Look for patterns across sources. What themes appear repeatedly? Where do sources agree or disagree?
M|Rese|**St|Cross-reference claims**
M|Rese|tx|For each major claim, verify it appears in the source material. Note which source supports each point.
M|Rese|**St|cr structured summary**
M|Rese|Orga|
M|Rese|it|Main claim
M|Rese|it|Supporting evidence from sources
M|Rese|it|Conflicting viewpoints (if any)
M|Rese|**St|Verify citations**
M|Rese|tx|Check that every claim references the correct source document. If citations are incomplete, return to Step 3.
M|Rese|tx|````
M|Rese|tx|This example shows how workflows apply to al tasks that don't require code. The checklist pattern works for any complex, multi-step process.
M|Rese|**Ex|PDF form filling workflow** (for Skills w/ code):
M|Rese|tx|````markdown  theme={null}
M|PDF |Copy|
M|PDF |tx|```
M|PDF |Task|
M|PDF |- [ |al the form (run analyze_form.py)
M|PDF |- [ |cr field mapping (edit fields.json)
M|PDF |- [ |Validate mapping (run validate_fields.py)
M|PDF |- [ |Fill the form (run fill_form.py)
M|PDF |- [ |Verify output (run verify_output.py)
M|PDF |tx|```
M|PDF |**St|al the form**
M|PDF |Run|`python scripts/analyze_form.py input.pdf`
M|PDF |tx|This extracts form fields and their locations, saving to `fields.json`.
M|PDF |**St|cr field mapping**
M|PDF |tx|Edit `fields.json` to add values for each field.
M|PDF |**St|Validate mapping**
M|PDF |Run|`python scripts/validate_fields.py fields.json`
M|PDF |tx|Fix any validation er before continuing.
M|PDF |**St|Fill the form**
M|PDF |Run|`python scripts/fill_form.py input.pdf fields.json output.pdf`
M|PDF |**St|Verify output**
M|PDF |Run|`python scripts/verify_output.py output.pdf`
M|PDF |tx|If verification fails, return to Step 2.
M|PDF |tx|````
M|PDF |tx|Clear steps prevent Claude from skipping ct validation. The checklist helps both Claude and you track progress through multi-step workflows.
M|Impl|**Co|Run validator → fix er → repeat
M|Impl|tx|This pattern greatly improves output qual.
M|Impl|**Ex|Style guide compliance** (for Skills w/o code):
M|Impl|tx|```markdown  theme={null}
M|Cont|tx|1. Draft your cn following the guidelines in STYLE_GUIDE.md
M|Cont|2. R|
M|Cont|it|Check terminology consistency
M|Cont|it|Verify examples follow the standard format
M|Cont|it|Confirm all required sections are present
M|Cont|3. I|
M|Cont|it|Note each issue w/ specific section reference
M|Cont|it|Revise the cn
M|Cont|it|rv the checklist again
M|Cont|tx|4. Only proceed when all requirements are met
M|Cont|tx|5. Finalize and save the document
M|Cont|tx|```
M|Cont|tx|This shows the validation loop pattern using reference documents instead of scripts. The "validator" is STYLE\_GUIDE.md, and Claude performs the check by reading and comparing.
M|Cont|**Ex|Document editing process** (for Skills w/ code):
M|Cont|tx|```markdown  theme={null}
M|Docu|tx|1. Make your edits to `word/document.xml`
M|Docu|2. *|`python ooxml/scripts/validate.py unpacked_dir/`
M|Docu|3. I|
M|Docu|it|rv the er message carefully
M|Docu|it|Fix the issues in the XML
M|Docu|it|Run validation again
M|Docu|tx|4. **Only proceed when validation passes**
M|Docu|5. R|`python ooxml/scripts/pack.py unpacked_dir/ output.docx`
M|Docu|tx|6. tst the output document
M|Docu|tx|```
M|Docu|tx|The validation loop catches er early.
